Risk Assessment: 

[width="100%",cols="50%,50%",]
|=======================================================================
|DESCRIPTION |Heart rate before and after up to 6mins of exercise

|RISKS a|
1. Asthma attack

2. Child running into things/people

3. Physical injury eg. falling

|ACTION TO BE TAKEN TO MINIMISE RISKS a|
1. Check child's asthma status with parent or with teacher (or with
child itself if old enough) before doing experiment. Do not allow child
to exercise if asthma is severe, and DO NOT ALLOW AN ASTHMATIC CHILD TO
DO EXPERIMENT IF THEY DO NOT HAVE AN INHALER.

2. Make sure exercise area is clear, use on-the-spot exercise e.g. star
jumps if space is limited

3. Demonstrator to ensure floor area is clear and dry. If area becomes
wet, locate a mop and dry the area.

|ACTION TO BE TAKEN IN THE EVENT OF AN ACCIDENT a|
1. Sit child down, keep them calm, locate inhaler for child to
self-administer. Call first aider.

2. Call first aider in case of injury

3. Call first aider in case of injury

